Dark and Lovely has done a voluntary recall of one of their products after they received complaints from hair users.  Earlier this week the National Consumer Commission (NCC) urged consumers in possession of certain Dark and Lovely Precise Diamond Straight and Shine relaxer 125 ml tubs with certain batch numbers “to immediately discontinue use of the product and return it to the point of sale for a full refund.”  The commission said they were informed by Dark and Lovely after they were alerted by 22 complaints from consumers.  Acting Consumer Commissioner, Ms Thezi Mabuza said Loreal, which owns Dark and Lovely, informed them of the voluntary recall.  “We urge South Africans who are in possession of Dark and Lovely Precise Diamond Straight and Shine relaxer 125 ml tub to return the product o the point of purchase for a refund.  ALSO READ: Frozen beans, stir fry recalled by McCain after glass found in limited batch “We understand that an isolated incident in the production led to an imbalance of the active raw material, affecting one batch only. Using the recalled product may lead to increased hair breakage, and increased scalp irritation,” she said.  Product: Dark and Lovely Precise Diamond Straight and Shine relaxer 125 ml tub.  Batch numbers: 87UD00  and 87UD01 Manufacturing date: December 2021, Expiry date: December 2023.  Take a look  The product has been distributed nationally and in neighbouring countries Botswana, Lesotho, Namibia, eSwatini, Zambia and Madagascar. Mabuza concluded as a commission they are urging suppliers and manufacturers to prioritize consumer safety at all times. The commission is monitoring the recall based on its recall guidelines.